# Getting Started Pages — Implementation Guide

How to build persona-specific onboarding pages for any new project using this template.
Each persona gets its own page with a quiz, checklist, and resource links — all in the same order and structure described below.

---

## Page Architecture

Every Getting Started page is built from the same shell:

```
GettingStarted[Persona].tsx        ← main page layout
[Persona]OnboardingQuiz.tsx        ← quiz component (separate file)
```

Both files live in `client/pages/component-library/` (or equivalent in your project).

The main page imports the quiz component and wires up the `onComplete` callback to handle conditional content that depends on quiz answers.

---

## Section Order — Every Persona Page

Follow this order exactly. Do not skip sections; hide them in collapsible accordions if they are not primary.

| # | Section | Type | Always visible? |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | Intro banner | Banner card | Yes |
| 2 | Resources card | Link grid | Yes |
| 3 | First steps checklist | Progress checklist | Yes (Designer) |
| 4 | Onboarding quiz | Interactive quiz | Yes |
| 5 | Conditional content | Card | Only when quiz answer triggers it |
| 6 | Before you prompt checklist | Progress checklist | Yes (PM) |
| 7 | How it works | Numbered step list | Visible card |
| 8 | Data / feature patterns | Grid of pattern cards | Visible card |
| 9 | Quick-start prompts | Collapsible accordion | Collapsed |
| 10 | Tips | Collapsible accordion | Collapsed |
| 11 | Key concepts / What the agent knows | Collapsible accordion | Collapsed |
| 12 | FAQ | Collapsible accordion | Collapsed |
| 13 | Using outside the tool / Key files | Collapsible accordion | Collapsed (bottom) |

> Not every persona needs every section. The Designer page omits "Before you prompt" and "Data patterns". The PM page omits "First steps" and "Key concepts". Add only what is relevant.

