## 1. Intro Banner

A colored card with a left border that sets context for the persona.

```tsx
<div style={{
  backgroundColor: 'var(--ld-semantic-color-fill-brand-subtle)',
  padding: '24px 32px',
  borderRadius: '8px',
  borderLeft: '5px solid var(--ld-semantic-color-border-brand)',
}}>
  <h3>For [Persona Name]</h3>
  <p>2–3 sentences explaining what this page helps them do.</p>
</div>
```

**Content formula:** Who it's for + what they'll accomplish + how the AI helps them.

---

## 2. Resources Card

A grid of clickable cards linking to external and internal resources. Always appears near the top, before the quiz.

**Structure:**
- Card has a colored top border (`border-top: 4px solid var(--ld-semantic-color-border-brand)`)
- Short heading + 1-sentence description above the grid
- Grid: `repeat(auto-fit, minmax(220px, 1fr))`
- Each link card: label (bold, link color) + short description + `↗` for external links

**Minimum resource links to include:**
1. Primary tool documentation (e.g., Builder.io Figma Plugin, PRD template)
2. Learning resource (e.g., Builder Academy, Figma Lunch & Learns)
3. Onboarding deck or slides (Figma)
4. Setup video (Vimeo)
5. Component Library Overview (`/component-library`)

**Airtable Figma Lunch & Learns link:**
`https://airtable.com/appEGZA2KCbx3A6IP/shr35BhsPf4bNULE1`

---

## 3. First Steps Checklist (Designer only)

A 3-item progress checklist that tracks the user's first actions.

```
[ ] Browse the Component Library to see what's available   → /component-library
[ ] Try the Component Sandbox to test a component live     → /component-library/component-tester
[ ] Copy a prompt from the quiz below and paste it into Fusion
```

**Implementation notes:**
- Use the LD `Checkbox` component (`@/components/ui/Checkbox`)
- Track checked state in a `Set<number>` via `useState`
- Show a progress bar (`doneCount / total * 100%`)
- Show a "Great start!" badge when all are checked
- Items with `href` render the label as an `<a>` link with strikethrough when checked

---

## 4. Onboarding Quiz

The quiz is a **separate component file** (`[Persona]OnboardingQuiz.tsx`).

### Quiz Shell Structure

Every quiz has the same 4 screens:

| Screen | Trigger | Content |
|---|---|---|
| Intro | `step === 0` | Feature cards + Start / Skip buttons |
| Questions | `step 1–N` | Progress bar + dots + question + options + nav |
| Result | `step === N+1` | Summary tags + generated prompt + reading path + Reset |

### Intro Screen Feature Cards (3 cards always)

```
⚡ [N] quick questions     → "Takes about 60 seconds"
📋 Ready-to-paste prompt   → "Copy directly into any AI agent"
🗺  Reading path           → "Know exactly which pages to visit first"
```

Use icons: `Flash`, `BulletList`, `Map` from `@/components/icons`.

CTA buttons: **"Start the quiz"** (primary) + **"Skip — generate a generic prompt"** (tertiary)

### Question Screen

Each question renders:
1. Progress indicator (bar + pill dots + "Question X of N" label + "Skip quiz" tertiary button)
2. Question title (`h4`, 18px bold)
3. Info alert: **"Why this matters:"** + explanation (`<Alert variant="info">`)
4. Radio options (`RadioGroup` + `Radio` from LD) — each option has bold label + subtitle description
5. Navigation: **Back** (secondary, disabled on Q1) | **Skip this question** (tertiary) | **Next / Generate prompt** (primary)

### Result Screen

1. Green success banner with `CheckCircleFill` icon + "Your personalized [persona] prompt is ready"
2. Summary tag pills (one per answered question, pill-shaped, subtle border)
3. Prompt box: header bar with "Copy prompt" button (primary → secondary with ✓ when copied) + italic prompt text
4. Reading path: brand-subtle header + numbered list of clickable component library pages
5. "Start over" button (secondary + `Refresh` icon, centered)

### onComplete Callback

The quiz accepts `onComplete?: (keyAnswer: string | undefined) => void`.
The parent page uses this to show conditional content based on one key answer (e.g., `hasPRD`).

```tsx
// In parent page:
const [quizAnswer, setQuizAnswer] = useState<string | undefined>(undefined);
<PersonaQuiz onComplete={setQuizAnswer} />
{quizAnswer === 'no' && <PRDTemplate />}
```

