## Designer Quiz — 5 Questions

**File:** `DesignerOnboardingQuiz.tsx`

| Q# | Question | Answer type | Options |
|---|---|---|---|
| 1 | What are you working on? | `featureType` | new-page, figma-code, explore, customize, other |
| 2 | Where are you starting from? | `startingPoint` | new, existing, figma, other |
| 3 | What's your primary goal right now? | `goal` | build, setup, explore, figma-to-code, other |
| 4 | Which tool are you working in? | `environment` | fusion, cursor, figma-make, developer |
| 5 | How would you describe your experience level? | `experience` | new, familiar, advanced, other |

**Reading path logic (based on `featureType`):**

| featureType | Suggested pages |
|---|---|
| `figma-code` | Icons, Buttons |
| `new-page` | Cards, Buttons |
| `explore` | Overview, Component Sandbox |
| `customize` | Guidelines |
| `other` | Overview, Getting Started |

Always add `Themes & Tokens` first unless `experience === 'advanced'`.

**Prompt generation:** Combine 4–5 paragraphs — one for featureType, one for startingPoint, one for goal, one for environment, one for experience level. Each paragraph is a direct instruction to the AI agent.

